          "{Accuracy: 0.86 - RF, Recall - 0.94 - DT or RF}",
          "Authors create separate classifiers while they could have treated this as either regression or Multiclass classification.\n\nAuthors also perform a Feature Importance analysis for both models created.\n\nLEarners that come from a more math heavy background are more likely to succeed.",
          "Double Binary classification which could have been converted into Regression or Multiclass classification. \n\nSurvivorship bias → sample can only consider learners who were accepted in the MSc.\n\nVery small dataset, from one cohort of students. \n\nOther metrics of evaluation could (and probably should) have been considered."
